    <text id="B0078T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Jackson informs William Woods that he owes Joseph Lewis $7.00 in rent.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Office 4th Division, 9th
                    Sub-District, Virginia.
                    <name type="recipient">William Woods <abbr expan="colored"
                        >(c)</abbr><lb/>Staunton</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-01-06"><abbr expan="January">Jan</abbr> 6 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, Va.,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>

                <p>Joseph Lewis <abbr expan="colored">(c)</abbr> states he cannot collect from you
                    rent of stable you occupy under agreement made <abbr expan="October">Oct</abbr>
                    14/67 which you propose to vacate <abbr expan="January">Jan</abbr> 8/68.</p>

                <p><abbr expan="Amount">Amt.</abbr> due from <abbr expan="October">Oct</abbr> 14/67
                    to <abbr expan="January">Jan</abbr> 8/68 2 <abbr expan="months">m</abbr>
                    &amp; 24 <abbr expan="days">d.</abbr> @ $2.50 per mo. is $7.00</p>

                <p>Please call at this office and pay above <abbr expan="amount">amt.</abbr> in full
                    or in part on or before Saturday <abbr expan="January">Jan</abbr> 11/68.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>Thos. P. Jackson<lb/> Agent</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript"><abbr expan="January">Jan</abbr> 8/68 Paid on <abbr
                            expan="account">act</abbr> of above $5.00 TPJ </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
